President Obama has nominated Danya Ariel Dayson, Peter Arno Krauthamer, and John Francis McCabe, Jr. to serve as Associate Justices of the Superior Court of the District of Columbia. Danya Ariel Dayson is an attorney with experience in both state and federal courts. She has represented criminal defendants in various cases and is involved in several legal organizations. Peter Arno Krauthamer is the Deputy Director for the Public Defender Service for the District of Columbia and has extensive experience in the legal field. John Francis McCabe, Jr. is a Magistrate Judge on the Superior Court of the District of Columbia, with experience in family court and criminal division.